I am just wondering if there is another site I can visit to find 
python examples for equilibrium calculations.  The link found on 
the "documentation" page at cantera.org is not working.  This link is:

http://rayleigh.cds.caltech.edu/%7Egoodwin/cantera/python/Cantera.html

I am new to cantera and python and would like some examples to learn 
from.  I am looking to use cantera to do some rough calculations 
involving adsorption of vapor phase Hg on various supports (the Hg 
will react with surface functional groups to form a stable surface 
species).

If anyone can provide any examples or lead me to a site where the 
examples that used to be held in the link above can be found, I would 
greatly appreciate it.


Thanks,

Dalton York
